 she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Tresedra was born in 1470, in Sidmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom. She married Nicholas Channon in 1485, in Sidmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1546, in her hometown, at the age of 76."},"et":{"1470–1546":"1470–1546","1470–1524":"1470–1524","1485–1524":"1485–1524","1524":"1524","1546":"1546","22 September 1524":"22. september 1524","1485":"1485","1470":"1470","Sidmouth, Devon, England":"Sidmouth, Devon, England","Sidmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Sidmouth, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sidbury, Devon, England":"Sidbury, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1470–1546":"1470–1546","1470–1524":"1470–1524","1485–1524":"1485–1524","1524":"1524","1546":"1546","22 September 1524":"22. syyskuuta 1524","1485":"1485","1470":"1470","Sidmouth, Devon, England":"Sidmouth, Devon, England","Sidmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Sidmouth, Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sidbury, Devon, England":"Sidbury, Devon, England"},"fr":{"1470–1546":"1470–1546","1470–1524":"1470–1524","1485–1524":"1485–1524","1524":"1524","1546":"1546","22 September 1524":"22 